e.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20want%20the%20predictability%20that%20comes%20with%20a%20fixed%20rate%20but%20are%20looking%20to%20spend%20less%20on%20interest%20over%20the%20life%20of%20your%20loan%2C%20a%2015-year%20fixed-rate%20mortgage%20might%20be%20a%20good%20fit%20for%20you.%20Because%20these%20terms%20are%20shorter%20and%20have%20lower%20rates%20than%2030-year%20fixed-rate%20mortgages%2C%20you%20could%20potentially%20save%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20in%20interest.%20However%2C%20you'll%20have%20a%20higher%20monthly%20payment%20than%20you%20would%20with%20a%20longer%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20Do%20Fed%20Rate%20Hikes%20Affect%20Mortgages%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Federal%20Reserve%20has%20increased%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-the-federal-funds-rate%5C%22%3Efederal%20funds%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%20dramatically%20to%20try%20to%20slow%20economic%20growth%20and%20get%20inflation%20under%20control.%20So%20far%2C%20inflation%20has%20slowed%20significantly%2C%20but%20it's%20still%20a%20bit%20above%20the%20Fed's%202%25%20target%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMortgage%20rates%20aren't%20directly%20impacted%20by%20changes%20to%20the%20federal%20funds%20rate%2C%20but%20they%20often%20trend%20up%20or%20down%20ahead%20of%20Fed%20policy%20moves.%20This%20is%20because%20mortgage%20rates%20change%20based%20on%20investor%20demand%20for%20mortgage-backed%20securities%2C%20and%20this%20demand%20is%20often%20impacted%20by%20how%20investors%20expect%20Fed%20hikes%20to%20affect%20the%20broader%20economy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed%20has%20indicated%20that%20it's%20likely%20done%20hiking%20rates%20and%20that%20it%20could%20start%20cutting%20this%20year.%20This%20would%20allow%20mortgage%20rates%20to%20trend%20down%20later%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhen%20Will%20Mortgage%20Rates%20Go%20Down%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMortgage%20rates%20increased%20dramatically%20over%20the%20last%20two%20years%2C%20but%20they're%20expected%20to%20go%20down%20at%20some%20point%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20April%202024%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-cpi-food-energy-gas-prices-consumer-price-index-2024-5%5C%22%3EConsumer%20Price%20Index%20rose%203.4%25%20year-over-year%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Inflation%20has%20slowed%20significantly%20since%20it%20peaked%20last%20year%2C%20but%20it%20has%20to%20slow%20further%20before%20rates%20can%20continue%20trending%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20homeowners%20looking%20to%C2%A0leverage%20their%20home's%20value%C2%A0to%20cover%20a%20big%20purchase%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20a%20home%20renovation%20%E2%80%94%20a%C2%A0home%20equity%20line%20of%20credit%20(HELOC)%20may%20be%20a%20good%20option%20while%20we%20wait%20for%20mortgage%20rates%20to%20ease.%20Check%20out%20some%20of%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-heloc-lenders%5C%22%3Ebest%20HELOC%20lenders%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20start%20your%20search%20for%20the%20right%20loan%20for%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20HELOC%20is%20a%20line%20of%20credit%20that%20lets%20you%20borrow%20against%20the%20equity%20in%20your%20home.%20It%20works%20similarly%20to%20a%20credit%20card%20in%20that%20you%20borrow%20what%20you%20need%20rather%20than%20getting%20the%20full%20amount%20you're%20borrowing%20in%20a%20lump%20sum.%20It%20also%20lets%20you%20tap%20into%20the%20money%20you%20have%20in%20your%20home%20without%20replacing%20your%20entire%20mortgage%2C%20like%20you'd%20do%20with%20a%20cash-out%20refinance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%22e3f3577dfe678e19f8dce895f3061b13%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcurrent-heloc-rates%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%22e3f3577dfe678e19f8dce895f3061b13%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%22100