aption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20technology%20to%20change%20the%20global%20balance%20of%20power%2C%20it%20needn't%20be%20new.%20It%20must%20simply%20be%20known.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%202017%2C%20the%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party%20has%20laid%20out%20careful%20plans%20to%20eventually%20dominate%20the%20creation%2C%20application%2C%20and%20dissemination%20of%20generative%20artificial%20intelligence%20%E2%80%94%20programs%20that%20use%20massive%20datasets%20to%20train%20themselves%20to%20recognize%20patterns%20so%20quickly%20that%20they%20appear%20to%20produce%20knowledge%20from%20nowhere.%20According%20to%20the%20CCP's%20plan%2C%20by%202020%2C%20China%20was%20supposed%20to%20have%20%26quot%3Bachieved%20iconic%20advances%20in%20AI%20models%20and%20methods%2C%20core%20devices%2C%20high-end%20equipment%2C%20and%20foundational%20software.%26quot%3B%20But%20the%20release%20of%20OpenAI's%20ChatGPT%20in%20fall%202022%20caught%20Beijing%20flat-footed.%20The%20virality%20of%20ChatGPT's%20launch%20asserted%20that%20US%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%20for%20the%20moment%20%E2%80%94%20were%20leading%20the%20AI%20race%20and%20threw%20a%20great-power%20competition%20that%20had%20been%20conducted%20in%20private%20into%20the%20open%20for%20all%20the%20world%20to%20see.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20guarantee%20that%20America's%20AI%20lead%20will%20last%20forever.%20China's%20national%20tech%20champions%20have%20joined%20the%20fray%20and%20managed%20to%20twist%20a%20technology%20that%20feeds%20on%20freewheeling%20information%20to%20fit%20neatly%20into%20China's%20constrained%20information%20bubble.%20Censorship%20requirements%20may%20slow%20China's%20AI%20development%20and%20limit%20the%20commercialization%20of%20domestic%20models%2C%20but%20they%20will%20not%20stop%20Beijing%20from%20benefiting%20from%20AI%20where%20it%20sees%20fit.%20China's%20leader%2C%20Xi%20Jinping%2C%20sees%20technology%20as%20the%20key%20to%20shaking%20his%20country%20out%20of%20its%20economic%20malaise.%20And%20even%20if%20China%20doesn't%20beat%20the%20US%20in%20the%20AI%20race%2C%20there's%20still%20great%20power%2C%20and%20likely%20danger%2C%20in%20it%20taking%20second%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20so%20much%20we%20can%20do%20with%20this%20technology.%20Beijing's%20just%20not%20encouraging%20consumer-facing%20interactions%2C%26quot%3B%20Reva%20Goujon%2C%20a%20director%20for%20client%20engagement%20on%20the%20consulting%20firm%20Rhodium%20Group's%20China%20advisory%20team%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BReal%20innovation%20is%20happening%20in%20China.%20We're%20not%20seeing%20a%20huge%20gap%20between%20the%20models%20Chinese%20companies%20have%20been%20able%20to%20roll%20out.%20It's%20not%20like%20all%20these%20tech%20innovators%20have%20disappeared.%20They're%20just%20channeling%20applications%20to%20hard%20science.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20internal%20documents%2C%20the%20CCP%20says%20that%20it%20will%20use%20AI%20to%20shape%20reality%20and%20tighten%20its%20grip%20on%20power%20within%20its%20borders%20%E2%80%94%20for%20political%20repression%2C%20surveillance%2C%20and%20monitoring%20dissent.%20We%20know%20that%20the%20party%20will%20also%20use%20AI%20to%20drive%20breakthroughs%20in%20industrial%20engineering%2C%20biotechnology%2C%20and%20other%20fields%20the%20CCP%20considers%20productive.%20In%20some%20of%20these%20use%20cases%2C%20it%20has%20already%20seen%20success.%20So%20even%20if%20it%20lags%20behind%20US%20tech%20by%20a%20few%20years%2C%20it%20can%20still%20have%20a%20powerful%20geopolitical%20impact.%20There%20are%20many%20like-minded%20leaders%20who%20also%20want%20to%20use%20the%20tools%20of%20the%20future%20to%20cement%20their%20authority%20in%20the%20present%20and%20distort%20the%20past.%20Beijing%20will%20be%20more%20than%20happy%20to%20facilitate%20that%20for%20them.%20China's%20vision%20for%20the%20future%20of%20AI%20is%20closed-sourced%2C%20tightly%20controlled%2C%20and%20available%20for%20export%20all%20around%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20world%20of%20modern%20AI%2C%20the%20technology%20is%20only%20as%20good%20as%20what%20it%20eats.%20ChatGPT%20and%20other%20large%20language%20models%20gorge%20on%20scores%20of%20web%20pages%2C%20news%20articles%2C%20and%20books.%20Sometimes%20this%20information%20gives%20the%20LLMs%20food%20poisoning%20%E2%80%94%20anyone%20who%20has%20played%20with%20a%20chatbot%20knows%20they%20sometimes%20hallucinate%20or%20tell%20lies.%20Given%20the%20size%20of%20the%20tech's%20appetite%2C%20figuring%20out%20what%20went%20wrong%20is%20much%20more%20complex%20than%20narrowing%20down%20the%20exact%20ingredient%20in%20your%20dinner%20that%20had%20you%20hugging%20your%20toilet%20at%202%20a.m.%20AI%20datasets%20are%20so%20vast%2C%20and%20the%20calculations%20so%20fast%2C%20that%20the%20companies%20controlling%20the%20models%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F05%2F21%2Ftechnology%2Fai-language-models-anthropic.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edo%20not%20know%20why%20they%20spit%20out%20bad%20results%2C%20and%20they%20may%20never%20know%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20a%20society%20like%20China%20%E2%80%94%20where%20information%20is%20tightly%20controlled%20%E2%80%94%20this%20inability%20to%20understand%20the%20guts%20of%20the%20models%20poses%20an%20existential%20problem%20for%20the%20CCP's%20grip%20on%20power%3A%20A%20chatbot%20could%20tell%20an%20uncomfortable%20truth%2C%20and%20no%20one%20will%20know%20why.%20The%20likelihood%20of%20that%20happening%20depends%20on%20the%20model%20it's%20trained%20on.%20To%20prevent%20this%2C%20Beijing%20is%20feeding%20AI%20with%20information%20that%20encourages%20positive%20%26quot%3Bsocial%20construction.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina's%20State%20Council%20wrote%20in%20its%202017%20Next%20Generation%20Artificial%20Intelligence%20Development%20Plan%20that%20AI%20would%20be%20able%20to%20%26quot%3Bgrasp%20group%20cognition%20and%20psychological%20changes%20in%20a%20timely%20manner%2C%26quot%3B%20which%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20means%20the%20tech%20could%20%26quot%3Bsignificantly%20elevate%20the%20capability%20and%20level%20of%20social%20governance%2C%20playing%20an%20irreplaceable%20role%20in%20effectively%20maintaining%20social%20stability.%26quot%3B%20That%20is%20to%20say%2C%20if%20built%20to%20the%20correct%20specifications%2C%20the%20CCP%20believes%20AI%20can%20be%20a%20tool%20to%20fortify%20its%20power.%20That%20is%20why%20this%20month%2C%20the%20Cyberspace%20Administration%20of%20China%2C%20the%20country's%20AI%20regulator%2C%20launched%20a%20chatbot%20trained%20entirely%20on%20Xi's%20political%20and%20economic%20philosophy%2C%20%26quot%3BXi%20Jinping%20Thought%20on%20Socialism%20with%20Chinese%20Characteristics%20for%20a%20New%20Era%26quot%3B%20(snappy%20name%2C%20I%20know).%20Perhaps%20it%20goes%20without%20saying%20that%20ChatGPT%20is%20not%20available%20for%20use%20in%20China%20or%20Hong%20Kong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Xi%20Jinping%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64147da75f4f5400191a1309%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221359%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20government%20of%20China%20has%20launched%20a%20chatbot%20trained%20entirely%20on%20Xi%20Jinping's%20political%20and%20economic%20philosophy.%3Cp%3EXie%20Huanchi%2FXinhua%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20CCP%2C%20finding%20a%20new%20means%20of%20mass%20surveillance%20and%20information%20domination%20couldn't%20come%20at%20a%20better%20time.%20Consider%20the%20Chinese%20economy.%20Wall%20Street%2C%20Washington%2C%20Brussels%2C%20and%20Berlin%20have%20accepted%20that%20the%20model%20that%20helped%20China%20grow%20into%20the%20world's%20second-largest%20economy%20has%20been%20worn%20out%20and%20that%20Beijing%20has%20yet%20to%20find%20anything%20to%20replace%20it.%20Building%20out%20infrastructure%20and%20industrial%20capacity%20no%20longer%20provides%20the%20same%20bang%20for%20the%20CCP's%20buck.%20The%20world%20is%20pushing%20back%20against%20China's%20exports%2C%20and%20the%20CCP's%20attempts%20to%20drive%20growth%20through%20domestic%20consumption%20have%20gone%20pretty%20much%20nowhere.%20The%20property%20market%20is%20distorted%20beyond%20recognition%2C%20growth%20has%20plateaued%2C%20and%20deflation%20is%20lingering%20like%20a%20troubled%20ghost.%20According%20to%20Freedom%20House%2C%20a%20human-rights%20monitor%2C%20Chinese%20people%20demonstrated%20against%20government%20policies%20in%20record%20numbers%20during%20the%20fourth%20quarter%20of%202023.%20The%20organization%20logged%20952%20dissent%20events%2C%20a%2050%25%20increase%20from%20the%20previous%20quarter.%20Seventy-eight%20percent%20of%20the%20demonstrations%20involved%20economic%20issues%2C%20such%20as%20housing%20or%20labor.%20If%20there's%20a%20better%20way%20to%20control%20people%2C%20Xi%20needs%20it%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsk%20the%20Cyberspace%20Administration%20of%20China's%20chatbot%20about%20these%20economic%20stumbles%2C%20and%20you'll%20just%20get%20a%20lecture%20on%20the%20difference%20between%20%26quot%3Btraditional%20productive%20forces%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bnew%20productive%20forces%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20buzzwords%20the%20CCP%20uses%20to%20blunt%20the%20trauma%20of%20China's%20diminished%20economic%20prospects.%20In%20fact%2C%20if%20you%20ask%20any%20chatbot%20operating%20in%20the%20country%2C%20it%20will%20tell%20you%20that%20Taiwan%20is%20a%20part%20of%20China%20(a%20controversial%20topic%20outside%20the%20country%2C%20to%20say%20the%20least).%20All%20chatbots%20collect%20information%20on%20the%20people%20who%20use%20them%20and%20the%20questions%20they%20ask.%20The%20CCP's%20elites%20will%20be%20able%20to%20use%20that%20information%20gathering%20and%20spreading%20to%20their%20advantage%20politically%20and%20economically%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20government%20doesn't%20plan%20to%20share%20that%20power%20with%20regular%20Chinese%20people.%20What%20the%20party%20sees%20will%20not%20be%20what%20the%20people%20see.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Chinese%20have%20great%20access%20to%20information%20around%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20Kenneth%20DeWoskin%2C%20a%20professor%20emeritus%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Michigan%20and%20senior%20China%20advisor%20to%20Deloitte%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it's%20always%20been%20a%20two-tiered%20information%20system.%20It%20has%20been%20for%202%2C000%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20ensure%20this%2C%20the%20CCP%20has%20constructed%20a%20system%20to%20regulate%20AI%20that%20is%20both%20flexible%20enough%20to%20evaluate%20large%20language%20models%20as%20they%20are%20created%20and%20draconian%20enough%20to%20control%20their%20outputs.%20Any%20AI%20disseminated%20for%20public%20consumption%20must%20be%20registered%20and%20approved%20by%20the%20CAC.%20Registration%20involves%20telling%20the%20administration%20things%20like%20which%20datasets%20the%20AI%20was%20trained%20on%20and%20what%20tests%20were%20run%20on%20it.%20The%20point%20is%20to%20set%20up%20controls%20that%20embrace%20some%20aspects%20of%20AI%2C%20while%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%20ideally%20%E2%80%94%20giving%20the%20CCP%20final%20approval%20on%20what%20it%20can%20and%20cannot%20create.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20real%20challenge%20of%20LLMs%20is%20that%20they%20are%20really%20the%20synthesis%20of%20two%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20Matt%20Sheehan%2C%20a%20researcher%20and%20fellow%20at%20the%20Carnegie%20Endowment%20for%20International%20Peace%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BThey%20might%20be%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20productivity%20growth%2C%20but%20they're%20also%20fundamentally%20a%20content-based%20system%2C%20taking%20content%20and%20spitting%20out%20content.%20And%20that's%20something%20the%20CCP%20considers%20frivolous.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20the%20party%20has%20shown%20that%20it%20can%20be%20ruthless%20in%20cutting%20out%20technology%20it%20considers%20%26quot%3Bfrivolous%26quot%3B%20or%20harmful%20to%20social%20cohesion.%20In%202021%2C%20it%20barred%20anyone%20under%2018%20from%20playing%20video%20games%20on%20the%20weekdays%2C%20paused%20the%20approval%20of%20new%20games%20for%20eight%20months%2C%20and%20then%20in%202023%20announced%20rules%20to%20reduce%20the%20public's%20spending%20on%20video%20games.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20AI%20is%20not%20simply%20entertainment%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20part%20of%20the%20future%20of%20computation.%20The%20CCP%20cannot%20deny%20the%20virality%20of%20what%20OpenAI's%20chatbot%20was%20able%20to%20achieve%2C%20its%20power%20in%20the%20US-China%20tech%20competition%2C%20or%20the%20potential%20for%20LLMs%20to%20boost%20economic%20growth%20and%20political%20power%20through%20lightning-speed%20information%20synthesis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20as%20Sheehan%20put%20it%2C%20the%20question%20is%3A%20%26quot%3BCan%20they%20sort%20of%20lobotomize%20AI%20and%20LLMs%20to%20make%20the%20information%20part%20a%20nonfactor%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnclear%2C%20but%20they're%20sure%20as%20hell%20going%20to%20try.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20CCP%20to%20actually%20have%20a%20powerful%20AI%20to%20control%2C%20the%20country%20needs%20to%20develop%20models%20that%20suit%20its%20purpose%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it's%20clear%20that%20China's%20tech%20giants%20are%20playing%20catch-up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20e-commerce%20giant%20Baidu%20claims%20that%20its%20chatbot%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinas-chatgpt-reportedly-bans-users-from-mentioning-winnie-the-pooh-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EErnie%20Bot%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20which%20was%20released%20to%20the%20public%20in%20August%20%E2%80%94%20has%20200%20million%20users%20and%2085%2C000%20enterprise%20clients.%20To%20put%20that%20in%20perspective%2C%20OpenAI%20generated%201.86%20billion%20visits%20in%20March%20alone.%20There's%20also%20the%20Kimi%20chatbot%20from%20Moonshot%20AI%2C%20a%20startup%20backed%20by%20Alibaba%20that%20launched%20in%20October.%20But%20both%20Ernie%20Bot%20and%20Kimi%20were%20only%20recently%20overshadowed%20by%20ByteDance's%20Doubao%20bot%2C%20which%20also%20launched%20in%20August.%20According%20to%20Bloomberg%2C%20it's%20now%20the%20most%20downloaded%20bot%20in%20the%20country%2C%20and%20it's%20obvious%20why%20%E2%80%94%20Doubao%20is%20cheaper%20than%20its%20competitors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20generative-AI%20industry%20is%20still%20in%20its%20early%20stages%20in%20China%2C%26quot%3B%20Paul%20Triolo%2C%20a%20partner%20for%20China%20and%20technology%20policy%20at%20the%20consultancy%20Albright%20Stonebridge%20Group%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20you%20have%20this%20cycle%20where%20you%20invest%20in%20infrastructure%2C%20train%2C%20and%20tweak%20models%2C%20get%20feedback%2C%20then%20you%20make%20an%20app%20that%20makes%20money.%20Chinese%20companies%20are%20now%20in%20the%20training%20and%20tweaking%20models%20phase.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20is%20which%20of%20these%20companies%20will%20actually%20make%20it%20to%20the%20moneymaking%20phase.%20The%20current%20price%20war%20is%20a%20race%20to%20the%20bottom%2C%20similar%20to%20what%20we've%20seen%20in%20the%20Chinese%20technology%20space%20before.%20Take%20the%20race%20to%20make%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-xi-jinping-crush-tesla-elon-musk-american-ev-industry-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eelectric%20vehicles%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20The%20Chinese%20government%20started%20by%20handing%20out%20cash%20to%20any%20company%20that%20could%20produce%20a%20design%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I%20mean%20any.%20It%20was%20a%20money%20orgy.%20Some%20of%20these%20cars%20never%20made%20it%20out%20of%20the%20blueprint%20stage.%20But%20slowly%2C%20the%20government%20stopped%20subsidizing%20design%2C%20then%20production.%20Then%20instead%2C%20it%20started%20to%20support%20the%20end%20consumer.%20Companies%20that%20couldn't%20actually%20make%20a%20car%20at%20a%20price%20point%20that%20consumers%20were%20willing%20to%20pay%20started%20dropping%20like%20flies.%20Eventually%2C%20a%20few%20companies%20started%20dominating%20the%20space%2C%20and%20now%20the%20Chinese%20EV%20industry%20is%20a%20manufacturing%20juggernaut.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilar%20top-down%20strategies%2C%20like%20China's%20plan%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-xi-jiinping-future-tech-global-economy-semiconductors-military-failing-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadvance%20semiconductor%20production%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20haven't%20been%20nearly%20as%20successful.%20Historically%2C%20DeWoskin%20told%20me%2C%20party-issued%20production%20mandates%20have%20%26quot%3Bgood%20and%20bad%20effects.%26quot%3B%20They%20have%20the%20ability%20to%20get%20universities%20and%20the%20private%20sector%20in%20on%20what%20the%20state%20wants%20to%20do%2C%20but%20sometimes%20these%20actors%20move%20slower%20than%20the%20market.%20Up%20until%202022%2C%20everyone%20in%20the%20AI%20competition%20was%20most%20concerned%20about%20the%20size%20of%20models%2C%20but%20the%20sector%20is%20now%20moving%20toward%20innovation%20in%20the%20effectiveness%20of%20data%20training%20and%20generative%20capacity.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20sometimes%20the%20CCP%20isn't%20skating%20to%20where%20the%20puck's%20going%20to%20be%20but%20to%20where%20it%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20also%20signs%20that%20the%20definition%20of%20success%20is%20changing%20to%20include%20models%20with%20very%20specific%20purposes.%20OpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%20said%20in%20a%20recent%20interview%20with%20the%20Brookings%20Institution%20that%2C%20for%20now%2C%20the%20models%20in%20most%20need%20of%20regulatory%20overhead%20are%20the%20largest%20ones.%20%26quot%3BBut%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20progress%20may%20surprise%20us%2C%20and%20you%20can%20imagine%20smaller%20models%20that%20can%20do%20impactful%20things.%26quot%3B%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EA%20targeted%20model%20can%20have%20a%20specific%20business%20use%20case.%20After%20spending%20decades%20analyzing%20how%20the%20CCP%20molds%20the%20Chinese%20economy%2C%20DeWoskin%20told%20me%20that%20he%20could%20envision%20a%20world%20where%20some%20of%20those%20targeted%20models%20were%20available%20to%20domestic%20companies%20operating%20in%20China%20but%20not%20to%20their%20foreign%20rivals.%20After%20all%2C%20Beijing%20has%20never%20been%20shy%20about%20using%20a%20home-field%20advantage.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-xi-jinping-crush-tesla-elon-musk-american-ev-industry-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJust%20ask%20Elon%20Musk%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20win%20the%20competition%20to%20build%20the%20most%20powerful%20AI%20in%20the%20world%2C%20China%20must%20combat%20not%20only%20the%20US%20but%20also%20its%20own%20instincts%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20technological%20innovation.%20A%20race%20to%20the%20bottom%20may%20simply%20beggar%20China's%20AI%20ecosystem.%20A%20rush%20to%20catch%20up%20to%20where%20the%20US%20already%20is%20%E2%80%94%20amid%20investor%20and%20government%20pressure%20to%20make%20money%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%20%E2%80%94%20may%20keep%20China's%20companies%20off%20the%20frontier%20of%20this%20tech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20base%20case%20for%20the%20way%20this%20goes%20forward%20is%20that%20maybe%20two%20Chinese%20entities%20push%20the%20frontier%2C%20and%20they%20get%20all%20the%20government%20support%2C%26quot%3B%20Sheehan%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20they're%20also%20burdened%20with%20dealing%20with%20the%20CCP%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eand%20a%20little%20slower-moving.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20to%20say%20we%20have%20nothing%20to%20learn%20from%20the%20way%20China%20is%20handling%20AI.%20Beijing%20has%20already%20set%20regulations%20for%20things%20like%20deepfakes%20and%20labeling%20around%20authenticity.%20Most%20importantly%2C%20China's%20system%20holds%20%3Cem%3Epeople%20%3C%2Fem%3Eaccountable%20for%20what%20AI%20does%20%E2%80%94%20people%20make%20the%20technology%2C%20and%20people%20should%20have%20to%20answer%20for%20what%20it%20does.%20The%20speed%20of%20AI's%20development%20demands%20a%20dynamic%2C%20consistent%20regulatory%20system%2C%20and%20while%20China's%20checks%20go%20too%20far%2C%20the%20current%20US%20regulatory%20framework%20lacks%20systemization.%20The%20Commerce%20Department%20announced%20an%20initiative%20last%20month%20around%20testing%20models%20for%20safety%2C%20and%20that's%20a%20good%20start%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20nearly%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20China%20has%20taught%20us%20anything%20about%20technology%2C%20it's%20that%20it%20doesn't%20have%20to%20make%20society%20freer%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20all%20about%20the%20will%20of%20the%20people%20who%20wield%20it.%20The%20Xi%20Jinping%20Thought%20chatbot%20is%20a%20warning.%20If%20China%20can%20make%20one%20for%20itself%2C%20it%20can%20use%20that%20base%20model%20to%20craft%20similar%20systems%20for%20authoritarians%20who%20want%20to%20limit%20the%20information%20scape%20in%20their%20societies.%20Already%2C%20some%20Chinese%20AI%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20like%20the%20state-owned%20iFlytek%2C%20a%20voice-recognition%20AI%20%E2%80%94%20have%20been%20hit%20with%20US%20sanctions%2C%20in%20part%2C%20for%20using%20their%20technology%20to%20spy%20on%20the%20Uyghur%20population%20in%20Xinjiang.%20For%20some%20governments%2C%20it%20won't%20matter%20if%20tech%20this%20useful%20is%20two%20or%20three%20generations%20behind%20a%20US%20counterpart.%20As%20for%20the%20chatbots%2C%20the%20models%20won't%20contain%20the%20sum%20total%20of%20human%20knowledge%2C%20but%20they%20will%20serve%20their%20purpose%3A%20The%20content%20will%20be%20censored%2C%20and%20the%20checks%20back%20to%20the%20CCP%20will%20clear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20the%20danger%20of%20the%20AI%20race.%20Maybe%20China%20won't%20draw%20from%20the%20massive%2C%20multifaceted%20AI%20datasets%20that%20the%20West%20will%20%E2%80%94%20its%20strict%20limits%20on%20what%20can%20go%20into%20and%20come%20out%20of%20these%20models%20will%20prevent%20that.%20Maybe%20China%20won't%20be%20pushing%20the%20cutting%20edge%20of%20what%20AI%20can%20achieve.%20But%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20Beijing%20can't%20foster%20the%20creation%20of%20specific%20models%20that%20could%20lead%20to%20advancements%20in%20fields%20like%20hard%20sciences%20and%20engineering.%20It%20can%20then%20control%20who%20gets%20access%20to%20those%20advancements%20within%20its%20borders%2C%20not%20just%20people%20but%20also%20multinational%20corporations.%20It%20can%20sell%20tools%20of%20control%2C%20surveillance%2C%20and%20content%20generation%20to%20regimes%20that%20wish%20to%20dominate%20their%20societies%20and%20are%20antagonistic%20to%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20an%20inflection%20point%20in%20the%20global%20information%20war.%20If%20social%20media%20harmfully%20siloed%20people%20into%20alternate%20universes%2C%20the%20Xi%20bot%20has%20demonstrated%20that%20AI%20can%20do%20that%20on%20steroids.%20It%20is%20a%20warning.%20The%20digital%20curtain%20AI%20can%20build%20in%20our%20imaginations%20will%20be%20much%20more%20impenetrable%20than%20iron%2C%20making%20it%20impossible%20for%20societies%20to%20cooperate%20in%20a%20shared%20future.%20Beijing%20is%20well%20aware%20of%20this%2C%20and%20it's%20already%20harnessing%20that%20power%20domestically%2C%20why%20not%20geopolitically%3F%20We%20need%20to%20think%20about%20all%20the%20ways%20Beijing%20can%20profit%20from%20AI%20now%20before%20its%20machines%20are%20turned%20on%20the%20world.%20Stability%20and%20reality%20depend%20on%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Flinette-lopez%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3ELinette%20Lopez%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0is%20