g%20in%20the%20mid-six%20figures%2C%20putting%20much%20of%20that%20money%20into%20various%20retirement%20and%20investment%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20working%20long%20weeks%2C%20he%20sold%20the%20company%20at%2032%20for%20seven%20figures%20and%20reached%20the%20amount%20he%20needed%20to%20retire%20comfortably%20while%20providing%20for%20his%20five%20kids.%20He%20said%20he%20was%20living%20on%20just%20%2430%2C000%20to%20%2440%2C000%20a%20year%2C%20as%20most%20of%20his%20earnings%20went%20to%20maxing%20out%20his%20retirement%20accounts%20and%20investing%20in%20real%20estate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20skipped%20over%20five%20years%20like%20it%20was%20nothing%2C%20but%20if%20you%20ask%20my%20wife%2C%20there%20were%20some%20extremely%20tough%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20gone%20a%20few%20nights%20a%20week%20at%20a%20minimum.%20I%20had%20operations%20all%20over%20Texas%20and%20Oklahoma.%20And%20I%20spent%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20trying%20to%20build%20up%20this%20company.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20this%20time%2C%20he%20acquired%20a%20real%20estate%20portfolio%20in%20Texas%2C%20taking%20advantage%20of%20house%20hacking%20and%20other%20strategies%20to%20have%20extra%20passive%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he%20was%20drained%20after%20years%20of%20nearly%20nonstop%20work%20and%20figured%20that%20he%20would%20never%20have%20this%20kind%20of%20freedom%20again%20after%20selling%20the%20company.%20He%20took%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomer-retiring-early-nervous-about-money-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emini-retirement%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20that%20included%20golfing%20as%20much%20as%20four%20times%20a%20week%2C%20skiing%2C%20playing%20basketball%2C%20and%20boating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20months%20in%2C%20he%20realized%20his%20hobbies%20were%20getting%20repetitive%20and%20boring.%20He%20felt%20disengaged%20from%20his%20work%20and%20social%20communities%2C%20and