Cp%3ECourtesy%20Dania%20Swails%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDania%20Swails%20found%20her%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20wasn't%20being%20read%20by%20applicant-tracking%20systems.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESwails%2C%20who's%20worked%20in%C2%A0finance%2C%20revamped%20her%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20to%20make%20it%20easier%20to%20get%20through.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20simplified%20her%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20format%20and%20has%20started%20to%20get%20more%20callbacks%20for%20job%20applications.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Fdania-s-9025807a%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EDania%20Swails%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%2028%2C%20has%20worked%20in%20finance%20and%20is%20looking%20for%20another%20job%20in%20the%20industry%20after%20leaving%20her%20last%20role.%20She%20has%20faced%20numerous%20rejections%20to%20jobs%20she's%20applied%20for.%20A%20recruiter%20suggested%20she%20rework%20her%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20so%20an%20applicant-tracking%20system%20might%20more%20easily%20read%20it.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20a%20bachelor's%20degree%20in%20sports%20management.%20I%20graduated%20in%202019%2C%20and%20the%20pandemic%20started%20in%20March%202020.%20So%2C%20some%20of%20the%20job%20offers%20I%20had%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20the%20prospects%20I%20had%20%E2%80%94%20weren't%20starting%20until%20the%20next%20season%2C%20but%20my%20opportunities%20went%20away%20because%20of%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20a%20friend%20who%20was%20a%20stockbroker.%20She%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%2C%20my%20job%20will%20train%20you%20to%20become%20a%20broker%20if%20that's%20something%20you're%20interested%20in.%26quot%3B%20At%20the%20time%2C%20I%20just%20needed%20a%20job.%20So%2C%20I%20became%20a%20broker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20into%20it%2C%20and%20I%20just%20%3Cem%3Ereally%3C%2Fem%3E%20liked%20it.%20I%20really%20liked%20finance.%20My%20dad%20works%20in%20finance%3B%20he%20does%20taxes%20and%20investing.%20He's%20told%20me%20my%20whole%20life%20that%20I%20need%20to%20look%20into%20finance.%20When%20I%20started%20in%20the%20industry%2C%20my%20dad%20and%20I%20used%20to%20study%20every%20night%20for%20my%20Series%207%20exam%2C%20which%20I%20passed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20working%20as%20a%20broker%2C%20I%20was%20recruited%20to%20be%20an%20equity%20trader.%20I%20really%20got%20into%20data%20and%20trends%20research%20when%20I%20was%20working%20at%20that%20job.%20I%20was%20there%20for%20two%20years%2C%20and%20then%20I%20got%20laid%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20I%20got%20laid%20off%2C%20I%20went%20on%20LinkedIn%20and%20found%20a%20job%20as%20an%20analyst.%20It%20was%20my%20first%20time%20not%20working%20with%20clients.%20I%20worked%20directly%20for%20the%20bank.%20I%20did%20like%20being%20an%20analyst%3B%20I%20just%20didn't%20like%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20felt%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20I've%20been%20in%20finance%20for%20four%20years.%20I've%20managed%20these%20accounts.%20I've%20done%20this.%20I%20haven't%20had%20a%20problem%20having%20a%20job.%26quot%3B%20So%2C%20at%20the%20end%20of%20January%2C%20I%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20burned%20out%20from%20this%20employer.%20I'll%20just%20leave.%20I'm%20sure%20I%20can%20find%20something%20else.%26quot%3B%20That%20didn't%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20a%20broker%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0a%20first-year%20broker%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0it%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20getting%20recruited%20on%20LinkedIn%20every%20day.%20That's%20how%20I%20got%20that%20job%20as%20an%20equity%20trader.%20And%2C%20even%20when%20I%20was%20laid%20off%2C%20I%20was%20only%20out%20of%20work%20for%20three%20weeks%2C%20and%20I%20was%20right%20back%20at%20work%20at%20a%20new%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20now%2C%20it's%20months%20later%2C%20and%20I%20still%20don't%20have%20a%20role.%20This%20has%20been%20the%20hardest%20it's%20ever%20been.%20I've%20never%20had%20an%20experience%20like%20this.%20LinkedIn%20had%20always%20been%20my%20best%20friend%2C%20but%20now%20it's%20my%20worst%20enemy%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0it's%20like%20a%20shift%20happened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f3ab9305-6d18-4c2a-9b71-c39e96a45baf%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ERevamping%20my%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20been%20told%20my%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20is%20impressive.%20I'd%20also%20been%20told%20it's%20too%20long%2C%20it's%20too%20short%2C%20it's%20too%20vague%2C%20and%20you%20need%20to%20change%20the%20formatting.%20I%20had%20my%20education%20and%20my%20skills%20on%20the%20side%2C%20along%20with%20my%20contact%20information.%20I%20had%20a%20template%20that%20was%20pretty%20fancy%20looking.%20I'd%20always%20used%20it%2C%20and%20I%20always%20thought%20that%20it%20had%20caught%20the%20recruiter's%20eye.%20But%20I%20just%20haven't%20been%20having%20much%20luck.%20So%2C%20I've%20been%20changing%20my%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0adding%20things%2C%20taking%20things%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20would%20be%20jobs%20where%20I%20met%20every%20requirement%2C%20and%20I%20was%20getting%20rejected%2C%20getting%20rejected%2C%20getting%20rejected.%20When%20I%20was%20an%20equity%20trader%2C%20I%20needed%20three%20to%20five%20years%20of%20experience%2C%20but%20they%20recruited%20me%2C%20and%20I%20only%20had%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half%20of%20experience.%20So%2C%20I%20was%20able%20to%20get%20into%20a%20higher%20role.%20And%20then%2C%20I%20became%20an%20analyst%20who%20needed%20a%20bit%20more%20experience%20than%20I%20had.%20But%20they%20said%20in%20the%20interview%20that%20they%20liked%20where%20my%20head%20was%20at%2C%20and%20so%20I%20got%20hired.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20I%20left%20my%20last%20job%2C%20I%20applied%20for%20roles%20where%20I%20didn't%20meet%20all%20the%20requirements%2C%20but%20I%20figured%20I%20could%20talk%20about%20my%20experience.%20I%20was%20getting%20automatically%20rejected%2C%20so%20I%20decided%20to%20apply%20only%20for%20jobs%20where%20I%20met%20every%20qualification.%20And%20I%20was%20still%20getting%20rejected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20here%20in%20Cincinnati%20now%20for%20four%20years.%20I%20like%20it%20but%20would%20also%20like%20to%20go%20somewhere%20else%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0maybe%20Miami%2C%20Philly%2C%20D.C.%2C%20or%20Chicago.%20I%20was%20applying%20for%20jobs%20and%20taking%20my%20address%20off%20my%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20so%20it%20wouldn't%20flag%20in%20the%20system.%20I%20was%20still%20not%20getting%20anything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20a%20recruiter%20I'd%20been%20working%20with%20said%20my%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20could%20be%20getting%20caught%20in%20applicant-tracking%20systems.%20She%20said%20I%20should%20put%20it%20through%20a%20system%20that%20will%20see%20if%20it%20flags%20when%20you%20compare%20it%20to%20a%20certain%20job%20description.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20submitted%20my%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20and%20job%20description%20through%20this%20system%2C%20I%20was%20surprised%20by%20the%20results.%20It%20said%20I%20had%20a%20low%20chance%20of%20getting%20the%20job.%20My%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20had%20dashes%2C%20which%20could%20have%20been%20throwing%20it%20off%20because%20an%20ATS%20sometimes%20doesn't%20recognize%20dashes.%20I%20also%20had%20more%20than%2032%20characters%20in%20the%20file%20name%2C%20and%20I%20was%20told%20that%20wasn't%20good%2C%20so%20I%20shortened%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recruiter%20said%20the%20formatting%20and%20template%20I%20used%20weren't%20reading%2C%20and%20the%20ATS%20wasn't%20picking%20up%20my%20key%20skills%20or%20education.%20I%20was%20also%20told%20that%20if%20it's%20over%20one%20page%2C%20but%20definitely%20two%2C%20it%20will%20kick%20it%20out%20automatically.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20had%20to%20revamp%20my%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20completely.%20I%20made%20it%20a%20simple%20document%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0basic%20black%20and%20white.%20Instead%20of%20having%20separate%20columns%2C%20it's%20straight%20up%20and%20down%20and%20in%20chronological%20order.%20It%20hasn't%20been%20that%20long%2C%20but%20I%20have%20had%20two%20callbacks%20since%20I%20updated%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20glad%20to%20have%20the%20new%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%2C%20but%20it%20also%20made%20me%20sad%2C%20honestly%2C%20because%20I%20feel%20like%20I%20missed%20out%20on%20many%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0especially%20ones%20that%20I%20really%20wanted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20yeah%2C%20I%20definitely%20will%20qualify%20for%20this.%26quot%3B%20I'd%20set%20my%20LinkedIn%20filters%3A%20I%20would%20apply%20for%20jobs%20that%20just%20opened%20in%20the%20past%2024%20hours%20with%20under%2010%20applicants.%20It's%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BOK%2C%20this%20only%20has%20three%20applicants.%20I%20meet%20all%20the%20requirements%20besides%20a%20bachelor's%20degree%20in%20finance.%26quot%3B%20I%20have%20the%20required%20experience.%20Then%2C%20my%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20was%20automatically%20rejected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227e95efe7-135a-4cb5-90ff-4bfca7e633a8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhere%20I%20go%20from%20here%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20I%20will%20probably%20keep%20both%20versions%20of%20my%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9.%20I%20want%20to%20have%20one%20that%20stands%20out%20when%20a%20person%20actually%20looks%20at%20it%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0that%20jumps%20out%20against%20all%20the%20other%20black-and-white%2C%20simpler%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s.%20And%20then%20I'll%20have%20the%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20I%20enter%20in%20the%20system%20for%20the%20ATS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20this%20just%20makes%20me%20feel%20like%2C%20what%20is%20the%20point%20of%20having%20recruiters%20if%20you're%20going%20to%20have%20a%20system%20that%20flags%20everything%3F%20I%20get%20it%20from%20an%20HR%20standpoint.%20If%20I%20were%20a%20recruiter%2C%20I%20would%20not%20want%20to%20go%20through%205%2C000%20applications.%20However%2C%20being%20someone%20who's%20job-seeking%2C%20this%20system%20doesn't%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20my%20last%20job%2C%20my%20mental%20health%20was%20just%20deteriorating.%20But%20I%20have%20a%20new%20source%20of%20stress%20now.%20Part%20of%20me%20feels%20like%20I'm%20being%20punished%20for%20not%20staying%20at%20my%20job%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0like%20I%20stuck%20my%20neck%20out%20too%20far.%20I%20wasn't%20arrogant%20when%20I%20left%2C%20but%20I%20did%20have%20the%20mindset%20that%20I%20could%20find%20something%20else%20because%20I%20have%20experience%20and%20I%20have%20a%20degree.%20And%20in%20the%20past%2C%20I%20was%20always%20getting%20recruited.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you've%20been%20unemployed%20for%20four%20months%2C%20you%20feel%20like%20maybe%20you%20were%20too%20arrogant.%20Maybe%20I%20wasn't%20humble%20enough.%20Maybe%20I%20should%20have%20stuck%20it%20out.%20Maybe%20I%20should%20have%20just%20stayed%20until%20there%20was%20something%20else.%20You%20have%20all%20these%20scenarios%20that%20go%20through%20your%20head%20when%20you're%20just%20not%20getting%20anything.%20It%20is%20very%20demoralizing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20when%20I%20apply%2C%20it%20often%20feels%20like%20it's%20just%20about%20what%20scans%20in%20the%20system.%20If%20you%20can%20get%20through%20the%20system%2C%20then%20you%20can%20prove%20yourself%20or%20have%20someone%20take%20a%20chance%20on%20you.%20But%20you%20have%20to%20get%20through%20the%20system%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobseeker-whose-resume-rejected-changed-format-to-help-search-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717320121000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F665a1f5d1cd3b177904237fb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobseeker-whose-resume-rejected-changed-format-to-help-search-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Dania%20Swails%20faced%20numerous%20job%20rejections.%20So%2C%20on%20a%20recruiter's%20advice%2C%20she%20revamped%20her%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20to%20make%20it%20more%20easily%20read%20by%20HR%20systems.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tparadis%40busi