0Santoriello%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BYou%20may%20have%20something%20really%20cool%20in%20your%20background%2C%20but%20if%20it's%20not%20relevant%20to%20this%20role%2C%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20take%20up%20your%20precious%20real%20estate%20on%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20with%20something%20that%20isn't%20going%20to%20be%20relevant%20to%20the%20hiring%20manager.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20average%2C%20Santoriello%20estimates%2C%20job%20seekers%20have%20roughly%20five%20seconds%20when%20a%20hiring%20manager%20looks%20at%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fex-google-recruiter-says-resumes-text-bricks-zero-chance-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Er%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%3C%2Fa%3E.%20So%20you%20want%20to%20ensure%20they%20can%20see%20what%20impact%2C%20value%2C%20and%20contribution%20you%20bring%20to%20the%20team%20in%20those%20five%20seconds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20best%20ways%20to%20do%20that%20when%20you're%20talking%20about%20what%20to%20keep%20and%20what%20to%20lose%20is%20you%20want%20to%20keep%20things%20that%20show%20results.%20Keep%20words%20like%20increased%2C%20decreased%2C%20drove%20revenue%2C%20successfully%2C%20efficiently%2C%20and%20streamlined.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAny%20of%20those%20action%20language%20words%20that%20lets%20the%20reader%20immediately%20see%20you've%20done%20something%2C%26quot%3B%20Santoriello%20said.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20put%20them%20at%20the%20front%20of%20the%20sentence%2C%20we%20don't%20want%20to%20bury%20it%20in%20the%20far%20right%20side%20of%20a%20sentence.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fc6abc27-d17c-4969-b2bd-c2182a22acb2%5C%22%3ELearn%20the%20language%20of%20hiring%20managers%20in%20your%20industry%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20comes%20in%20especially%20handy%20when%20considering%20a%20career%20change%20and%20trying%20to%20describe%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvaluable-transferrable-skills-of-the-future-2013-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etransferrable%20skills%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20new%20industry%2C%20according%20to%20Santoriello.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20write%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20toward%20the%20new%20industry%2C%20you%20want%20to%20use%20the%20industry%20specific%20language%2C%26quot%3B%20Santoriello%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20about%20showing%20them%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0not%20telling%2C%20showing%20them%20%E2%80%94%20that%20you%20understand%20how%20your%20skill%20transfers%20and%20use%20that%20language%20to%20support%20that.%20It%20doesn't%20mean%20that%20the%2015%20years%20you've%20spent%20in%20tech%20aren't%20relevant%20now%20that%20you%20want%20to%20go%20into%20medical%20research.%20There's%20probably%20a%20whole%20lot%20of%20skill%20there%20that's%20relevant.%20We%20just%20need%20to%20formulate%20it%20and%20put%20it%20in%20the%20language%20that%20the%20new%20industry%20understands.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20noted%20that%20this%20is%20where%20a%20career%20coach%20really%20can%20help%2C%20but%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20describing%20the%20language%20of%20your%20chosen%20industry%2C%20it's%20time%20to%20%26quot%3Bplay%20with%20your%20best%20friend%20Google.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20when%20I%20say%20play%2C%20I%20mean%20play%2C%20have%20fun.%20Go%20down%20rabbit%20holes%2C%20do%20the%20research%2C%20spend%20the%20time%20getting%20lost%20reading%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-linkedin-got-weird-work-life-blurred-lines-of-oversharing-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earticles%20on%20LinkedIn%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20Santoriello%20said.%20%26quot%3BJoin%20groups%20specific%20to%20where%20you%20want%20to%20go%20%E2%80%94%20both%20digital%20and%20face-to-face%20if%20that's%20your%20thing.%20Check%20out%20trade%20associations.%20There's%20so%20much%20information%20available%20today.%20When%20I'm%20working%20with%20my%20members%2C%20I%20say%20this%20t